import { useEffect } from "react"; export default function Swiper() { useEffect(() => { const swiper = new Swiper(".mySwiper", { effect: "coverflow", grabCursor: true, centeredSlides: true, slidesPerView: "auto", coverflowEffect: { rotate: 15, stretch: 0, depth: 300, modifier: 1, slideShadows: true, }, loop: true, }); // Cleanup function if needed return () => { swiper.destroy(); }; }, []); // Empty dependency array ensures this effect runs only once on mount return (
); }
